Angola’s Banco BIC May Expand to Congo, Namibia, Chairman Says

-- B y   C a n d i d o   M e n d e s
-- 
2011-09-06T16:43:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/angola-s-banco-bic-may-expand-to-congo-namibia-chairman-says.html
Banco BIC Angola , the country’s
fourth-biggest bank in terms of deposits, is considering
expanding into neighboring countries including  Namibia  and the
 Democratic Republic  of Congo, said Chairman Fernando Teles.  The Luanda-based lender is studying legislation, the
economy and opportunities in those countries, Teles said in an
e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candido Mendes in Luanda at 
 cmendes6@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 